#: src/administration/install_docker.md:1
msgid "Install with Docker"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:3
msgid ""
"Make sure you have both docker and docker-compose(>=`2.0`) installed. On "
"Ubuntu, just run `apt install docker-compose-v2 docker.io`. On Debian, you "
"need to install Docker [using their official installation instructions and "
"custom `apt` repo](https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/debian/)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:5
msgid ""
"Create a folder for the lemmy files. the location doesnt matter. You can put "
"this anywhere you want, for example under `/srv/`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:12
msgid "Then download default config files:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:21
msgid ""
"Edit `docker-compose.yml` and `lemmy.hjson` to replace all occurrences of "
"`{{ domain }}` with your actual Lemmy domain, `{{ postgres_password }}` with "
"a random password."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:23
msgid ""
"Also edit `nginx_internal.conf` and replace `{{ nginx_internal_resolver }}` "
"with `127.0.0.11` (use `10.89.0.1` for RedHat distributions)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:25
msgid ""
"If you'd like further customization, have a look at the [config file]"
"(configuration.md) named `lemmy.hjson`, and adjust it accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:27
msgid "Database tweaks"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:29
msgid "To optimize your database, add this file."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:31
msgid ""
"You can input your system specs, using this tool: https://pgtune.leopard.in."
"ua/"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/install_docker.md:33
msgid ""
"`wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LemmyNet/lemmy-ansible/main/examples/"
"customPostgresql.conf`"
msgstr ""

